      <section eId="sec_CCP-3658">
        <num>CCP 3658</num>
        <heading>3658.  Same; requisites</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCP-3658__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The plaintiff had possession or precarious possession of the immovable property
or real right therein at the time the disturbance occurred.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-3658__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The plaintiff and his ancestors in title, or the person for whom the plaintiff
possesses precariously and that person's ancestors in title, had such possession quietly and
without interruption for more than a year immediately prior to the disturbance, unless evicted
by force or fraud.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-3658__subsec_3">
          <num>(3)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The disturbance was one in fact or in law, as defined in Article 3659.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-3658__subsec_4">
          <num>(4)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The possessory action was instituted within a year of the disturbance.
Amended by</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=111824</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
